cfg BoolOpt sync power state during shutdown
Determine whether to sync instance power states during nova compute service
When set to True the nova compute service will sync instance power
Setting this option to True will interfere with use of the
resume guests state on host boot configuration option and cause it not
to work as expected In order to resume previously running guests on host
boot the power state in the database is used to identify guests that were
previously running If sync power state during shutdown is set to
True the power state in the database will be updated to indicate the
guests are shutdown Thus they will not be resumed during host boot even
when resume guests state on host boot is set to True In summary
these two options are mutually exclusive
True nova compute will sync instance power states during a graceful
False nova compute will not sync instance power states during a
graceful shutdown of the service this is the default behavior
sync power state during shutdown timeout
resume guests state on host boot

Generic policy check string for system administrators These are the people
who need the highest level of authorization to operate the deployment
They re allowed to create read update or delete any system specific
resource They can also operate on project specific resources where
applicable e g cleaning up baremetal hosts
SYSTEM ADMIN role admin and system scope all
Generic policy check string for system users who don t require all the
authorization that system administrators typically have This persona or
check string typically isn t used by default but it s existence it useful
in the event a deployment wants to offload some administrative action from
SYSTEM MEMBER role member and system scope all
Generic policy check string for read only access to system level resources
This persona is useful for someone who needs access for auditing or even
support These uses are also able to view project specific resources where
applicable e g listing all volumes in the deployment regardless of the
SYSTEM READER role reader and system scope all
This check string is reserved for actions that require the highest level of
authorization on a project or resources within the project e g setting the
default volume type for a project
PROJECT ADMIN role admin and project id project id s
This check string is the primary use case for typical end users who are
working with resources that belong to a project e g creating volumes and
PROJECT MEMBER role member and project id project id s
This check string should only be used to protect read only project specific
resources It should not be used to protect APIs that make writable changes
e g updating a volume or deleting a backup
PROJECT READER role reader and project id project id s

brief The QObjectComputedProperty class is a template class that helps porting old
properties to the bindable property system
QObjectComputedProperty is a read only property which is recomputed on each read
It does not contain a storage of a value
It is one of the Qt internal classes implementing l Qt Bindable Properties
The rules for getters in l Bindable Property Getters and Setters
also apply for QObjectComputedProperty Especially the getter must not be
the callback given to the QObjectComputedProperty as this will usually
not read from the QObjectComputedProperty object
No setter is required or allowed as QObjectComputedProperty is read only
To correctly participate in dependency handling QObjectComputedProperty
has to know when its value the result of the callback given to it might
have changed It is the developer s responsibility to call markDirty
on the QObjectComputedProperty object whenever this might be the case
Note that calling markDirty might trigger change handlers in dependent
properties which might in turn use the object the QObjectComputedProperty
is a member of So markDirty must not be called when being in a transition
If there is any input to the computation of this property which might
change without notice like for example file contents
